        'Tiny Dancer' was originally recorded in 1971 and appeared on Elton's 'Madman Across the Water' album.
        Diana died in 1997 26 years later.

        The song is about lyricist Bernie Taupin's girlfriend who he later married. She travelled with Elton and his band on tour apparently sewing together their stage costumes.
